race.comment: STORMBRINGER (3) is promising and was quickly back in the winners' stall, taking out a 60 here over 1300m. Peaks now, and he's the one to beat if he races here instead of Rosehill Sunday. AHELLBENDA (12) has raced in stronger and has been unlucky not to have broken through. Is third up off narrow defeats at Goulburn and Gosford last time, and with the extra fitness will be right in it. TELLING (4) is improving and was beaten less than 2L at Gosford 24 days ago. Has a wide gate to contend with, but he's a player with average luck. Fellow Sydneysider SUPAIRO (8) missed a nose at Nowra at 58 level as favourite, and carries 3kg less in this. Has an awkward barrier, but he rates well enough to feature. THE EYES HAVE IT (16) sits at the bottom of the weights and would be a hope if she gets a start.
